{"000-section": {"000-title": "Kerala Education Loan Repayment Scheme Launched"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Highlights of Kerala Education Loan Repayment Scheme", "001-listElement": "- The scheme will apply to loans whose repayment began before April 1, 2016.", "002-listElement": "- The government will bear 90 percent of the amount repayable during the first year and 75 percent in the second year.", "003-listElement": "- 50 percent of the repayable amount in the third year and 25 percent in the fourth year would be borne by govt.", "004-listElement": "- For loans up to Rs 4 lakh which were deemed non-performing assets before March 31, 2016, the government will bear 60 per cent of the principal amount. The remaining 40 per cent has to be borne by the loanee.", "005-listElement": "- For loans between Rs 4 lakh and Rs 9 lakh that have turned NPAs, the state government will shoulder 50 percent of the principal amount, subject to a maximum of Rs 2.4 lakh."}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Kerala ELRS Guidelines", "001-normal": "The detailed guidelines of Kerala education loan repayment scheme can be downloaded from the official website at [elrs.kerala.gov.in](https://sarkariyojana.com/kerala-education-loan-repayment-scheme-2017-registration-application-forms/) using the below link.  \n Operational Guidelines of Scheme", "002-normal": "The education loan repayment scheme of Kerala Government would benefit those with total household income of not more than Rs. 6 Lakh per annum and have availed no more than Rs. 9 Lakh in education loan. Under the scheme, 60% of the loan repayment amount would be borne by the state government while rest 40% would have to be borne by the student itself.", "003-normal": "The banks would have to waive interest on the loan and penal interest to avail repayment from the bank."}}